To start, I like what I see. Sounds and looks great for a port. The auto fire option was a good feature and doesn't cheapen the game one bit, as it just takes care of the menial part of game play. However, the touch control option is too slow for thumb control, and takes multiple swipes to move the ship across the screen, while the static dpad is never a good option and leads to constant accidental collisions.. If an option to turn up the sensitivity were added so you can move the ship across the screen in a single stroke of the thumb it would greatly help. Also add an option to use a floating dpad instead of just static.

Great presentation of a classic shooter, I'd give it the edge slightly over the original. It suffers slightly with the control issues of the original, touch screen controls are good but you end up blocking the screen and there can be a LOT going on you need to avoid. The on screen Dpad is handy but I don't find diagonals register very well.  This is a game that really needs an external controller to avoid any frustration. Classic game though, well presented and well worth the money :)
